## 🔍 Topic Distribution Example

When testing a document, the model produces topic scores such as:

```
Topic 0: 0.0000
Topic 1: 0.0000
Topic 2: 0.6394
Topic 3: 0.0000
```

This means:

* The document belongs strongly to Topic 2
* It has no meaningful relation to other topics

Due to the small and clean dataset, documents usually belong to one dominant topic.

